INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (194, 1, '2014-01-24 23:55:25', '2014-01-24 23:55:25', '<h2>Payments</h2>\r\nCurrently we accept Visa, Mastercard, Discovery and American Express, Paypal, money orders or personal checks.\r\n\r\nOrders made with money order or personal check will be processed once payments clear. Â If we donâ€™t receive your payment with 2 weeks after the order has been placed, your order will be removed.\r\n<h3>Layaway</h3>\r\nBecause we want our rings to be accessible to everyone who wants one, we do offer payment plans.\r\n\r\nTo get started we require a 15% deposit. Â Also an additional 10% layaway fee will be applied to the total of the ring. Â If the ring youâ€™d live has a gem stone, we also require the cost of the stone be paid for in the deposit, since we donâ€™t keep stones in stock.\r\n\r\nOnce the deposit has been paid you can pay as much as youâ€™d like, as often as youâ€™d like. Â Your order will be processed and shipped once the we receive full payment.\r\n<h2>Shipping</h2>\r\nDue to demand, the current turnaround time for each order is 11-14 weeks. Â Both domestic and international orders are shipped via USPS First Class. Â Once your order ships, youâ€™ll receive an email along with a tracking number. Â Also each order will require a signature for delivery.\r\n\r\nActual shipping times vary based on location.\r\n<h3>Shipping times</h3>\r\nDomestic orders are shipping via USPS First Class, and delivered within 3 days in most cases.\r\n\r\nInternational orders are shipped USPS First Class International. Â Ship time varies greatly depending on the country being shipping, so we cannot give you an estimated time of delivery. Â Also, we are not responsive for duties or taxes incurred on international orders.\r\n\r\nInternational orders are shipped USPS Priority Mail Express International, and generally take 3 to 5 business days depending on your location. Â We are not responsive for duties or taxes incurred on international orders.\r\n<h3>Insurance</h3>\r\nWe want to protect our work and your ring as much as possible during shipping, therefore add insurance by default to every order. Â No matter what, your shipment is protected.\r\n\r\nInsurance against loss, rifling, and damage can be purchased at an additional cost depending on the purchased value. We cannot be responsible for items, lost or stolen, once they leave here\r\n\r\nInsurance can be added during checkout process.\r\n<h2>Refunds and Exchanges</h2>\r\nBecause each piece is crafted by hand and usually made to order, we do not give refunds.\r\n\r\nIf you would like to return a ring for any reason, it has to been returned with 7 business days. Â The ring must be in itâ€™s original conditional condition without any scratches, dents, dings, etc. Â Weâ€™ll happily give you 50% of the price of the returned ring to be used towards a new ring.\r\n\r\nBecause of the current demand, and out of respect to other customers, your new ring will be made in the same turnaround time as before.\r\n\r\nIf your ring is engraved and does not fit properly we have to charge full price for a new ring because it cannot be resold.\r\n<h3>Wrong size?</h3>\r\nFor wood rings, if you ordered the wrong size, your ring will probably have to be remade. Â In certain cases it may be possible to go down as much as a half size, or up as much as a full size.\r\n\r\nFor metal rings, a simple resize is $40. Â If the adjustment requires that the wood inlay be replace, then thereâ€™s a $200 charge to do the resizing and replace the wood inlay. Â If the ring canâ€™t be resized, then weâ€™ll give you 60% of the price of the original ring to be used towards remaking the ring, as long as the ring is returned in itâ€™s original condition.\r\n<h2>Refinishing and Repairs</h2>\r\nIf youâ€™d like to send by your ring for refinishing or repairs, please enclose $7 ($30 for international customers) to cover shipping costs. Â If money isnâ€™t enclosed, then we canâ€™t ship your ring back to you.\r\n