INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (206, 1, '2014-01-29 22:35:18', '2014-01-29 22:35:18', '<b>How long does a wooden ring last?</b>\r\n\r\nYour wooden ring is made of a bentwood fashion. Â This entails manipulating the grain of the wood to be fashioned into a circle. Â This encircling of the wood gives the ring a prevailing strength over rings turned on a lathe.\r\n\r\nWith proper care your ring will last a lifetime. A hardwood floor in a house will last well over 100 years with proper care. It\'s the same with a wood ring.\r\n\r\nTo us, proper care looks like taking off your ring while working with tools, gardening, and anything else that will scratch your ring. Â This will help to preserve your ring. Â Also remember to keep it polished with the wax that we provide with each ring.\r\n\r\nEventually, your ring will need to be refinished, just like a hardwood floor. Â We will happily refinish your ring for you at no extra cost to you.\r\n\r\n<b>How do I know my ring size?</b>\r\n\r\nWooden rings are measured by the same American standard as a metal rings. We recommend going to at least two local jewelers to be measured. This also provides opportunity to try on rings and see what width feels comfortable to you.\r\n<pre><b>Do not use a printable ring sizer from the internet. With these, the sizing is extremely inaccurate.</b></pre>\r\n<b>What if I order the wrong size? Can a wood ring be resized or exchanged?</b>\r\n\r\nIf you ordered the wrong size, your ring will probably have to be remade. Â In certain cases it may be possible to go down as much as a half size, or up as much as a full size.\r\n\r\nThe good news is if you return the ring in its original condition, we will happily give you a 50% credit towards a new ring. Â We love you that much!\r\n\r\n<b>How long is the turnaround time on made-to-order rings?</b>\r\n\r\nAt the moment, Jonathan personally makes each ring, single-handedly. Â In order to ensure quality and add his personal touch, the turnaround time for mad